1.1.name: wordpress/custom-menu
1.1.description: This plugin allows you to display a custom menu that you've created in your theme's "Menus" section in a post or page. Use [menu name="Menu Name"] in your post or page to insert the custom menu. The "name" attribute is required. Since version 1.2, you can now provide a "title" attribute to add a header title to your custom menu (e.g. [menu name="Menu Name" title="My Menu"].)
